INFLUENZA (09): CANADA (ALBERTA) H1N1, ANIMAL, FELINE
*****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: 7 Feb 2014
Source: CBC.ca [edited]
http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/calgary/cat-death-from-h1n1-confirmed-by-calgary-veterinary-school-1.2527610


The University of Calgary veterinary school has diagnosed a fatal case of H1N1 in a domestic cat. The cat was one of 2 that died in a Calgary household. These are believed to be the 1st feline cases of pH1N1-09 in Canada, the university said in a release.

The flu shot offers good protection against serious illness for 2014. The flu strain has been reported sporadically in cats, ferrets, and dogs in other countries.

It is assumed that the route of transmission was from humans to cat. There are no known reports of cat-to-human transmission, but that risk cannot be excluded by veterinarians, the university said.

