******
[2]
Date: 7 Feb 2014
Source: 660News.com [edited]
http://www.660news.com/2014/02/07/pair-of-cats-found-to-have-h1n1-virus/


Two cats in the city have died recently as a result of the H1N1 flu virus. It is believed the animals picked up the virus from someone visiting the family over the holidays.

Dr Alistair Cribb at the U of C Faculty of Veterinary Medicine said they are spreading the word: "We've communicated this out to the veterinary community in Alberta because they need to be aware in case they see cats," Cribb said. "We've all known this was a possibility, and we've informed the chief provincial veterinarian who has informed Alberta Health."

These are the 1st cases in Canada, but Cribb notes that there is not a serious risk for cats or dogs. There is no proof the animals can spread the virus to people.

[byline: Kenny Mason]

