[ProMED-mail last reported a confirmed 2009 H1N1 influenza infection in a pet in 2011. These new cases serve as a reminder that the virus is still circulating in the population and is still capable of infecting people and pets.

Readers are encouraged to view the various resources available regarding influenza in your cat by viewing the moderator's comments in ProMED-mail posting 20110215.0500.

The province of Alberta, Canada may be found on the interactive HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at http://healthmap.org/r/a6HJ. - Mod.TG]
